A 14-year-old boy who was allegedly set ablaze by his elder brothers has died while undergoing treatment at the Mandera Teaching and Referral hospital, police say.  The minor succumbed to burns early Wednesday morning, the Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) confirmed.  According to DCI, the minor was a witness to a robbery, where his elder brothers were suspects.  “The boy, a class seven pupil at a local primary school in Mandera was set ablaze by his elder brothers who feared that he might testify against one of them, accused of stealing a mobile phone,” police said.  Fire reported at Moi High School Kabarak  Police rescue boy set ablaze by his two brothers  Why mob justice is wrong and can land you into big trouble  Nakuru: Man charged with wife’s gruesome murder DCI officers had on Tuesday rushed to their home in Mandera to try and contain the fire, rescuing the boy who had sustained serious burns.  Authorities arrested his two brothers, 17 and 20 years old, who had gone into hiding following the incident.   Police say the duo is currently being held at Mandera Police station and will be “processed for the offence of Murder.”    Drought in Mandera: Famiiies facing starvation in Mandera with hundreds of livestock dead  #CROSSFIRE: Murathe, Salat, Kositany & Kang'ata discuss BBI , fate of DP Ruto and 2022 politics-FULL  Kang'ata clarifies the contents of his letter to the president in relation to BBI billV By Winfrey Owino | 1 day ago By Abdimalik Ismail Hajir | 1 day ago By Mate Tongola | 6 days ago By Moses Nyamori | 8 days ago